.SH NAME
\fB²DPROG² \- Appointment import\fR: reads an appointment list exported as PDF and records the appointments in a MariaDB database
.br
(manpage-Hilfe in deutsch verfügbar: 'man ²DPROG²' oder 'man -Lde ²DPROG²')
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fB²DPROG² [-<shortopt>|--<longopt> [<supplement>]] ...\fR
.SH SHORT DESCRIPTION
\fB²DPROG²\fR is a command line program that converts a fixed PDF file (default: \fB/DATA/Patientendokumente/plz/TMFTools.pdf\fR, an appointment list export) into text using \fBLibreOffice\fR (headless), reads the tabular appointments contained in it (no., patient no., weekday, date, time, patient, appointment type, note) and records them in the MariaDB table \fBtermine\fR.
.br
The program is suited for the regular synchronisation of an externally maintained appointment list (e.g. from a scheduling module) with an own database, e.g. for further analysis or display.
.SH INSTALLATION
.br
First, please read the chapters 'Functionality', 'Preconditions', 'Automatically installed software packages' and 'Implications' below. Then, if connected to the internet, call (e.g. by copying the line and pasting it into a terminal):
.br
\fBN=²DPROG²;P=${N}_inst.sh;cd ~;wget https://raw.githubusercontent.com/²gitv²/$N/master/install.sh -O$P&&sh $P\fR
.br
At last, call:
.br
 \fB²DPROG²\fR
.br
and answer some questions of the program.
.SH USAGE
Ideally, the program should have installed itself after the first call(s) and one-time answering of some questions in a self-running way.
.br
The program is typically called periodically via \fBcron\fR (option \fB-cm\fR/\fB--cronminutes\fR). At each call it checks whether the source PDF file is newer than the last processed state (based on the field \fBabgerufen\fR in the table \fBtermine\fR); only then it is reconverted and re-read. \fB-f\fR/\fB--force\fR forces re-reading regardless of the timestamp.
.br
New appointments are inserted into the table \fBtermine\fR within a transaction.
