.SH FUNCTIONALITY
.LP
When called, '\fB²DPROG²\fR' accomplishes the following:
.LP
\fB1)\fR General and program-specific defaults are set.
.LP
\fB2)\fR Defaults are loaded from the configuration file, if it exists (default: \fB²DPROG².conf\fR in the same directory as \fB²DPROG²\fR, default: \fB/usr/local/sbin/²DPROG²\fR).
.LP
\fB3)\fR Command line arguments are evaluated and override the configuration file where applicable.
.LP
\fB4)\fR Questions are asked if values are missing or an interactive option is set.
.LP
\fB5)\fR The program inserts itself if wanted and necessary into root's \fBcrontab\fR in order to be called in adjustable intervals.
.LP
\fB6)\fR The MariaDB database is initialised and the table \fBtermine\fR is checked and if necessary created or amended.
.LP
\fB7)\fR The source PDF file is converted to a text file with \fBsoffice --headless --convert-to txt\fR if needed (only if the PDF is newer than an existing text file); special characters (umlauts, ß) are converted back from the PDF-internal encoding.
.LP
\fB8)\fR The modification date of the PDF file is compared with the most recent retrieval timestamp (\fBMAX(abgerufen)\fR) stored in the table \fBtermine\fR. If the file is not newer, processing is aborted — unless \fB-f\fR (\fB--force\fR) is set.
.LP
\fB9)\fR Otherwise the text file is read line by line. Based on the header line (columns \fBNr.\fR, \fBPNr.\fR, \fBTag\fR, \fBDatum\fR, \fBUhr\fR, \fBPatient\fR, \fBTerminart\fR, \fBZusatz\fR) the column positions are determined; each subsequent line is split into its fields based on these positions.
.LP
\fB10)\fR Within a database transaction, the found appointments are inserted into the table \fBtermine\fR, each with the current time as \fBabgerufen\fR.
.LP
\fB11)\fR The configuration file is written if necessary.
.LP
\fB12)\fR If the option \fB-autoupd\fR is active, the program's version number is compared with that of the installation source and, if behind, an update is performed.
.SH PRECONDITIONS
\fBHardware\fR: Access (filesystem or network share) to the source PDF file containing the exported appointment list.
.br
\fBSoftware\fR: The program is adjusted to an installation of Opensuse >= 42.1, Debian >= 9, Ubuntu >= 16.04, Mint >= 18 or Fedora >= 24 with standard options. System D must be installed. One of the packet managers \fBapt\fR, \fBdnf\fR, \fByum\fR or \fBzypper\fR must be installed. The program '\fBwget\fR' must be installed. MariaDB must be running. \fBLibreOffice\fR (command line tool \fBsoffice\fR) is required for the PDF conversion.
